org.jcvi.jillion.trace.fastq

Class FastqFileParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.trace.fastq.FastqFileParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FastqParser

    public abstract class FastqFileParser
extends Object
implements FastqParser
    Contains factory methods to create new FastqParser objects that will parse a single fastq encoded file or InputStream and call the appropriate visitXXX methods on the given FastqVisitor. The implementations of the public factory methods only support the simplest most common usecases of fastq files and parsing fastq files.
    1. Each fastq record is assumed to be only 4 lines long
    2. No records have comments on the defline
    3. FastqVisitor.FastqVisitorCallback.FastqVisitorMementos are not supported
    If these restrictions do not properly describe your fastq file to be parsed or you want to use FastqVisitor.FastqVisitorCallback.FastqVisitorMementos, then please use the FastqFileParserBuilder object instead which has additional configuration options to support all of these features but comes with a performance penality.
    Author:
    dkatzel
    See Also:
    FastqFileParserBuilder

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static FastqParser create(InputStream in)
        Create a new FastqFileParser instance that will parse the given fastq encoded inputStream that does not contain defline comments and is only 4 lines per fastq record. Please Note that inputStream implementations of the FastqFileParser can not create FastqVisitor.FastqVisitorCallback.FastqVisitorMementos or use #parse(FastqVisitor, FastqVisitorMemento) method.

        If you need to parse Fastq files that have comments or have more than 4 lines per record please use FastqFileParserBuilder which has additional configuration options.

        Parameters:
        in - the fastq encoded inputstream to parse.
        Returns:
        a new FastqParser instance; will never be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if inputstream is null.
        See Also:
        FastqFileParserBuilder.FastqFileParserBuilder(InputStream)

      • create

        public static FastqParser create(File fastq)
                          throws IOException
        Create a new FastqFileParser instance that will parse the given fastq encoded File which may be zipped or gzipped, but does not contain defline comments and is only 4 lines per fastq record. Please Note the returned implementations of the FastqFileParser can not create FastqVisitor.FastqVisitorCallback.FastqVisitorMementos or use #parse(FastqVisitor, FastqVisitorMemento) method.

        If you need to parse Fastq files that have comments or have more than 4 lines per record or you want to use FastqVisitor.FastqVisitorCallback.FastqVisitorMementos please use FastqFileParserBuilder which has additional configuration options.

        Parameters:
        fastq - the fastq encoded file to parse; must exist and be readable; may be a "normal" fastq file, or zipped or gzipped.
        Returns:
        a new FastqParser instance; will never be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if fastq is null.
        IOException - if fastq does not exist or is not readable.
        See Also:
        FastqFileParserBuilder.FastqFileParserBuilder(File)
